link:labelLink.link:label: Party Demographics
Party Contact Details Category Type Code
A code which identifies the type of contact details category for a party.
Valid values are: Geographic = Geographic Contact Details Telephonic = Telephonic Contact Details Electronic = Electronic Contact Details Contact = Authorised Contact Details
Party Contact Details Usage Type Code
A code which identifies the usage type of contact details for a party.

Valid values are: POS = Postal Address RES = Residential Address BUS = Business Address BHN = Business Hours Number MOB = Mobile Number AHN = After Hours Number FAX = Fax EML = Email INET = Internet address ESA = Electronic Service Delivery Address MGOV = myGov Details ACBHN = Authorised Contact Business Hours Number ACMOB = Authorised Contact Mobile Number ACAHN = Authorised Contact After Hours Number ACFAX = Authorised Contact Fax ACEML = Authorised Contact Email
Party Entity Relationship End Date
The date when a relationship between two entities ends.
Party Entity Relationship Start Date
The date when a relationship between two entities commences.
Party Entity Relationship Type Code
A code which identifies the relationship between an entity and an associate.

Valid values are: PTNRSHP-PTNR = Partnership to Partner PTNR-PTNRSHP = Partner to Partnership LTDPTNRSHP-PTNR = Limited Partnership to Partner PTNR-LTDPTNRSHP = Partner to Limited Partnership CMP-DTR = Company to Director DTR-CMP = Director to Company CMP-PBLOFFCR = Company to Public Officer PBLOFFCR-CMP = Public Officer to Company CMP-OFFCBRR = Company to Office Bearer OFFCBRR-CMP = Office Bearer to Company CMP-TRSTEE = Company to Trustee TRSTEE-CMP = Trustee to Company TRST-TRSTEE = Trust to Trustee TRSTEE-TRST = Trustee to Trust SF-TRSTEE = Superannuation Fund to Trustee TRSTEE-SF = Trustee to Superannuation Fund SF-TRSTEEDTR = Superannuation Fund to Trustee Director TRSTEEDTR-SF = Trustee Director to Superannuation Fund SF-MBR = Superannuation Fund to Member MBR-SF = Member to Superannuation Fund
